&lt;p&gt;Would you like to be part of a service which is innovative, forward-thinking and committed to enabling people who are experiencing eating disorders to recover and discover their potential?&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are seeking to appoint 1 band 6 RMN with caring, compassionate nature, who are innovative, creative, flexible and highly motivated. Primarily you will undertake specialist assessments and therapeutic work and physical health care for people presenting with eating disorders in East Lancashire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be an excellent communicator and team player, with the successful applicant joining a dynamic multi-disciplinary team of professionals working across East Lancashire with base in Nelson.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is an exciting time and a chance to work in this specialist all age service – if this sounds like something you wish to be involved in, please contact those highlighted below who will happily discuss this further.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Regular clinical supervision and support will be provided.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
